%spark2.pyspark

# pyspark(sparksql) demo for having a quick data exploratory and machine learning
# THE FIRST STAGE  -->DATA EXPLORATORY

# read source adata into a data frame
pedf=spark.read.format("csv").options(delimiter=',',header='true',inferschema='true').load('/user/spark/data.csv')

#Get info about attribute names and types
pedf.printSchema()

# register pedf to a temp view and run sql on it to explore data
pedf.createOrReplaceTempView("pedfv")

#Take a look how data looks like
spark.sql("select * from pedfv").show(5)

#Use describe function to get the basic statitics number like min, max,stddev

pedf.describe().show()

%spark2.pyspark

# THE SECOND STAGE --> DATA PREPARATION

from pyspark.ml.feature import VectorAssembler

v=VectorAssembler()
v.setInputCols(["AT","V","AP","RH"])
v.setOutputCol("features")

%spark2.pyspark

# THE THRID STAGE --> DECIDE DATA MODELING

# Split the data set into traning and test data set with ratio 80:20

seed=12345
(testset,trainset) =pedf.randomSplit([0.2,0.8],seed)

# Apply Linear Regression MOdel

from pyspark.ml.regression import LinearRegression
from pyspark.ml import Pipeline

lr=LinearRegression()
lr.setPredictionCol("PR_PE").setLabelCol("PE").setFeaturesCol("features").setMaxIter(10).setRegParam(0.1)

lrp=Pipeline()
lrp.setStages([v,lr])

lrm=lrp.fit(trainset)
results=lrm.transform(testset).select("AT","V","AP","RH","PE","PR_PE")
results.show(5)

%spark2.pyspark

# compute RMSE and R2  as evaluation metric for the testdata

from pyspark.ml.evaluation import RegressionEvaluator

eval= RegressionEvaluator(predictionCol="PR_PE",labelCol="PE",metricName="rmse")

myrmse=eval.evaluate(results)
print("Root Mean Squared Error: %.2f" % myrmse)


myr2=eval.evaluate(results, {eval.metricName:"r2"})

print("r2: {:.2f}".format(myr2))

results.createOrReplaceTempView("resultsv")
rmse_results=spark.sql("select pe, pr_pe, pe-pr_pe as residual_error, (pe-pr_pe)/pe as within_rsme from resultsv")
rmse_results.show(5)
rmse_results.createOrReplaceTempView("rmse_resultsv")

%pyspark

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt


spark.sql("select within_rsme from rmse_resultsv").toPandas().hist(bins=20)

plt.ylabel('Density')
plt.xlabel('Within_RSME')
plt.title('Histogram of Within_RSME')
